  "text": "Object B was also a rectangle composed of 9 smaller rectangles with spaces of 1 pixel between them (this was a software requirement). When object A contacted object B, object A continued to move to the right at 2.7 cm s -1 and the 9 small rectangles dispersed at 13.5 cm s -1 . Motion continued until all 9 rectangles has exited the frame. This stimulus usually gives rise to an impression that object A smashes object B to pieces [CITATION_1] .",
